C","target":"recSRPfTSaf7TsRiN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recMs3SHZ5C9skUDe","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"reckMG16ukBhsbJ0Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recqk9LM9GPdK91aw","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recgkFqZovgbr3pAi","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"reckKYeZ5P0KFuSkB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recpCMN0bRpzByjaR","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recp7x7eelYoC2eJC","target":"recODnfv69EyvRMvA","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recihY2yXKK8bSnPk","ref":"Acts.24.1","text":"And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders, and with a certain orator named Tertullus, who informed the governor against Paul.","year":60},{"id":"rec47ryXMQEz2uBFR","ref":"Acts.24.2","text":"And when he was called forth, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, Seeing that by thee we enjoy great quietness, and that very worthy deeds are done unto this nation by thy providence,","year":60},{"id":"rec2YO42zRuw1VTtH","ref":"Acts.24.3","text":"We accept it always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness.","year":60},{"id":"rec11GtlifadcLUw3","ref":"Acts.24.4","text":"Notwithstanding, that I be not further tedious unto thee, I pray thee that thou wouldest hear us of thy clemency a few words.","year":60},{"id":"recnmaZ3SqIG0bgFa","ref":"Acts.24.5","text":"For we have found this man a pestilent fellow, and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes:","year":60},{"id":"recYvOlB2VvH3gcyl","ref":"Acts.24.6","text":"Who also hath gone about to profane the temple: whom we took, and would have judged according to our law.","year":60},{"id":"recaR8zOdI6kH7Fg9","ref":"Acts.24.7","text":"But the chief captain Lysias came upon us, and with great violence took him away out of our hands,","year":60},{"id":"recd39y7e7NvHSpae","ref":"Acts.24.8","text":"Commanding his accusers to come unto thee: by examining of whom thyself mayest take knowledge of all these things, whereof we accuse him.","year":60}]}
